item.title: US-163 West - Distance Marker
item.description: First distance marker along US-163 west. Distance to Mexican Hat and Monument Valley (Navajo Tribal Park).

item.title: US-191 South at US-163
item.description: US-191 South at US-163 in San Juan County. Turn left to continue south on US-191 to Mexican Water (Arizona). Continue straight for US-163 west to Mexican Hat. This is the eastern end of US-163 west.

item.title: US-160 West at US-163 and Navajo IR-591
item.description: US-160 West at US-163 and Navajo IR-591. Turn right for US-163 east; turn left for Navajo IR-591.

item.title: US-160 West at US-163
item.description: US-160 West at US-163 in Kayenta. Use US-163 north for Kayenta and Mexican Hat. Use US-160 west for Tuba City. This is the western end of US-163.

item.title: US-160 West Approachign US-163
item.description: US-160 west approaching US-163. US-163 is incorrectly marked here as AZ-163.

item.title: US-160 East at US-163
item.description: US-160 east approaching US-163 to Mexican Hat and Kayenta. Continue east on US-160 for US-191.

item.title: End UT-161 South at US-163
item.description: End of UT-261 at US-163 north of Mexican Hat.

item.title: End UT-261 South at US-163
item.description: Direction sign to Bluff via US-163 east, at the end of UT-261 near Mexican Hat.

item.title: US-160 East at US-163
item.description: US-160 east approaching US-163 to Mexican Hat, in Kayenta.

item.title: US-160 East at US-163/BIA-591
item.description: US-160 east at US-163/BIA-591 junction in Kayenta.
